  <!-- SEO Content + FAQ -->
  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>What is a Markdown Editor?</h2>
    <p>A markdown editor is a specialized text editor for writing content in Markdown — the lightweight markup language created by John Gruber. Markdown uses simple, intuitive syntax like <code>#</code> for headings, <code>**</code> for bold, and <code>*</code> for italic text. This online markdown editor gives you a live preview panel that renders your Markdown as HTML in real time, so you can see exactly how your document will look as you write it.</p>

    <h2>Why Use an Online Markdown Editor?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No installation required:</strong> Write Markdown directly in your browser without downloading or installing any software.</li>
      <li><strong>Live preview:</strong> See the rendered output side-by-side as you type, catching formatting issues immediately.</li>
